headline: Costco Tariff Lawsuits Could Reshape Costs And Cash For Members
summary: Costco Wholesale (NasdaqGS:COST) is among more than 1,800 companies suing for tariff refunds after several of President Trump's tariffs were struck down by the Supreme Court. The lawsuits seek to reclaim tariff-related payments that companies, including Costco, previously made on affected imports. A favorable outcome could lead to material refunds and influence how Costco manages its future cost structure. Costco Wholesale, known for its membership based warehouse clubs and bulk sales...
